# src/presentation/

The **presentation layer** — the surface that an outside caller (user,
script, peer service) interacts with. It translates between external wire
formats and the application layer's use-case API.

Belongs here:
- HTTP route handlers / controllers
- CLI command definitions and argument parsing
- gRPC service implementations
- Request/response DTOs and serializers
- Input validation (shape, types, missing fields)
- View models / view templates

Does **not** belong here:
- Business rules (live in `../domain/`)
- Multi-step workflows or transactions (live in `../application/`)
- Concrete I/O backends (live in `../infrastructure/`)

A handler in this layer should be thin: parse the request, call an
application service, format the response, return.

Canonical reference: `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/general/architecture.md`.
